nity.origam.com/uploads/default/original/2X/c/cb614764a8f149c4fbcafe22d6b810f913becef3.png","https://community.origam.com/uploads/default/original/2X/9/95d203d3c6e21bada04df1178cf10902d860fd83.png","https://community.origam.com/uploads/default/original/2X/6/6ca2bb7c3c9cc0c21b4fd2098198f0d0eebf2e30.png","https://community.origam.com/uploads/default/original/2X/8/87c03b7f7308301506081ca2ddbce75fef4ce173.png","https://community.origam.com/uploads/default/original/2X/b/bad528f5052ba91933f488f0546f4f93845893ec.png","https://community.origam.com/uploads/default/original/2X/5/593717e944f5d73c0641c39a44159a08d84ccb5a.png","https://community.origam.com/uploads/default/original/2X/e/e99317b6379f9d507cbbd0321638f74073d84f3c.png","https://community.origam.com/uploads/default/original/2X/f/f20ce6c5801a644f405ca9681661358a8c4d2ea6.png","https://community.origam.com/uploads/default/original/2X/e/e9a43d568e994bea442acda86f22efb10b6d8dae.png","https://community.origam.com/uploads/default/original/2X/a/a38621fd4b9d785b7700e2d0f24add674c234577.png","https://community.origam.com/uploads/default/original/2X/e/efb0e59ac8bd2ec231bba3e77da507c131eacb4a.png","https://community.origam.com/uploads/default/original/2X/b/be765f98cd8c362962fa3b3988f21b41a68ed223.png","https://community.origam.com/uploads/default/original/2X/0/0b472fd8dcc99735fe02aa6815e11a9cb28a41e4.png"]},"payload":{"url":"","schema":"20231218A","file":"content.txt","text":"# How to create Screens\n\nURL: https://community.origam.com/t/how-to-create-screens/3952\n\n@vikter (2025-02-14 11:06:41Z):\n   \n This guide will walk you through the process of creating user screens based on screen sections. \n A user screen in ORIGAM is composed of one or more screen sections, where each screen section serves as a separate \u201Ccontainer\u201D for displaying data from one or more different entities. \n For example, imagine a partner directory, where one section contains data about the partner (e.g., company name, address, etc.), and another section contains information about individual contact persons and their details (e.g., name, surname, phone, email, etc.). \n \n [!success]- Prerequisites for further work \n To follow along, you must meet the following five basic prerequisites: \n \n  Running database server  \n  Running ORIGAM Server  \n  Project created in ORIGAM Architect  \n  Entities and fields created  \n  Running client application in your browser  \n \n Once these prerequisites are set up, log into the client application using the  username and password you created  during the project setup. \n \n You can create screens using a wizard (action) or by manually setting them up. \n   Screen with Action \n To create a screen using a wizard, simply right-click on the entity in the Model Browser for which you want to create a screen, then select  Actions  /  Create Screen : \n  \n\n\n[Image: https://community.origam.com/uploads/default/original/2X/d/dd1c12fd0afa2f47725ae7df10a31eb4048d657a.png]\nDescription: The image depicts a Model Browser interface for a software application titled \u0022myapplication.\u0022 Visible sections include \u0022Common,\u0022 \u0022Data,\u0022 and \u0022Entities.\u0022 Under \u0022Entities,\u0022 several items are listed, such as two folders labeled \u0022__Origam General Interfaces\u0022 and \u0022__system,\u0022 along with \u0022Dimensions\u0022 and \u0022myapplication,\u0022 where \u0022Priority\u0022 is highlighted. A context menu is displayed with options including \u0022Create Lookup...,\u0022 \u0022Create Screen...,\u0022 and \u0022Create Menu Item...\u0022 among others. The purpose of the UI appears to be for managing data structures and entities within the application, facilitating various actions related to data organization and UI component creation.\n\n\n  \n A wizard will then appear: \n  \n\n\n[Image: https://community.origam.com/uploads/default/original/2X/0/0e6e4fc0b8cf51eef004420a7f948df017532155.png]\nDescription: The image depicts a user interface dialog titled \u0022Create Screen Wizard,\u0022 indicating that the user is in a process to create a screen based on an entity. The main text states, \u0022What will happen...\u0022 followed by \u0022Create Screen on Entity.\u0022 It describes that the wizard will generate essential elements for the menu\u0027s functionality, including three items: Data Structure (marked with a circle), Screen Section (marked with a square), and Screen (marked with a square). Two buttons are present at the bottom: \u0022Next\u0022 and \u0022Cancel.\u0022 The overall purpose is to guide the user through the screen creation process within a software application.\n\n\n  \n To create a screen, the wizard will also need to create a screen section and a data structure for it. \n In the next step, name your screen and choose the fields you want to include. In addition to the fields you\u2019ve created, default fields that hold meta information (such as who created the record and when) are also included: \n  \n\n\n[Image: https://community.origam.com/uploads/default/original/2X/5/5b26d2a5ceced274f59aba70511cb84625ab57b7.png]\nDescription: The image displays a user interface for a \u0022Create Screen Wizard\u0022 application. The title section indicates the purpose of the interface, prompting users to \u0022Please Select Fields.\u0022 Users can choose fields to be displayed on the screen from a list on the left, where options like \u0022_mockPk,\u0022 \u0022Color,\u0022 \u0022Id,\u0022 \u0022Name,\u0022 and \u0022Order\u0022 are shown, with \u0022Name\u0022 and \u0022Order\u0022 checked. Additional fields include \u0022RecordCreated,\u0022 \u0022RecordCreatedBy,\u0022 \u0022RecordUpdated,\u0022 \u0022RecordUpdatedBy,\u0022 and \u0022Selected,\u0022 which are unchecked. There is a caption field labeled \u0022Caption:\u0022 where the word \u0022Priority\u0022 is entered. At the bottom, there are two buttons labeled \u0022Next\u0022 and \u0022Cancel,\u0022 indicating the next step in the process. The interface is designed for field selection in a data management context.\n\n\n  \n In the next step, you will see a summary of what you are about to create: \n  \n\n\n[Image: https://community.origam.com/uploads/default/original/2X/4/4a45626e23e109760c7f509d55ee6ce0d9a22024.","vector_provider":"AI.Ollama.OllamaTextEmbeddingGenerator","vector_generator":"__","last_update":"2026-05-01T23:48:38"},"vector":[0.0041808034,0.0020463504,-0.06521445,-0.01285914,0.0034424479,-0.008656641,-0.020745689,-0.015838295,-0.0002362976,-0.009409767,0.04295702,0.0009543072,-0.015857207,0.029803844,-0.007187374,-0.023358759,0.008727617,0.015137976,0.047522634,0.00570034,-0.018631158,-0.021672513,0.039978646,0.021120816,0.015257431,0.056381546,0.002555609,-0.02170463,0.025614947,-0.022605859,-0.0051457966,-0.0527218,0.017504496,-0.008689523,-0.0068894746,-0.015635997,-0.013943723,-0.010503842,-0.038227446,-0.0021101066,-0.01738794,-0.006451237,-0.006349991,0.020658838,-0.05045847,-0.04937997,0.022228865,0.0021349208,0.033432726,-0.052444927,-0.043270435,0.018897872,0.051353082,-0.03643294,0.046077613,0.058043916,-0.05166518,0.008575442,-0.053400204,0.036195155,-0.020841984,0.003558321,-0.020241389,-0.025658129,0.024913609,0.006324115,-0.031067263,0.0026893606,-0.02788933,-0.034718968,-0.024244877,0.050067913,-0.025806796,-0.030719327,-0.0964876,0.010583021,-0.015541167,0.0047338647,-0.06110635,0.012742212,-0.037886925,-0.020382322,0.013178238,0.0022227538,0.02553235,-0.007896116,-0.051322214,0.10189303,0.041475013,0.03588882,-0.041655723,-0.01936635,0.07134341,-0.052368917,-0.0076045,-0.010544571,-0.03142888,-0.0025862963,0.0007174283,0.025361009,-0.032399934,-0.025570208,-0.0488365,-0.011319334,-0.03650666,-0.008822916,0.0025954118,-0.009633863,-0.019519337,-0.03675425,0.0018555652,0.012926554,0.010769817,-0.013607313,0.026881516,-0.01187318,0.010190245,-0.028251057,-0.0044939127,0.0073107714,-0.03367299,0.0572638,0.0584438,-0.024648733,0.02032088,0.019810917,-0.011367483,-0.0